{"key":"post-14403916","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14403916</id>\n<content>Never seal or silicone a light fixture.&amp;nbsp; Moisture will still get in and then the water that condenses will be trapped.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There should be no electronics in a humidifier.&amp;nbsp; Put it on the bottom shelf, or floor.&amp;nbsp; A CFL lamp can burn in a high humidity location.&amp;nbsp; Keep it open and not sealed though.&amp;nbsp; Avoid spraying the fixture.&amp;nbsp; LED lamps are another option.&amp;nbsp; Get 'cool white', and the more power the better up to a point.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14405455</next>\n<prev>14403275</prev>\n<first>14402845</first>\n<last>14405455</last>\n<when>1304600623</when>\n<utime>05/05/11 04:03 PM</utime>\n</post>"}